<tr>
<td bgcolor="#EEEEEE" colspan=2 class=news>
<table><tr><td valign=top><img src='images/icon_hl.gif' alt='Halflife' border=0></td><td width="100%" valign=top>First off, the <A HREF="http://www.planethalflife.com/uncrossable/" target=_new>Uncrossable Parallel</A> mod has been split in 2, here's the post they made:<br><br><span class=quote>"Uncrossable Parallel, a respected and long term development project has launched a new offshoot within the "UP" franchise, Uncrossable Parallel: Close Quarters Combat. The new project will begin development immediately with a brand new team that will work along side the existing UP team, sharing UP technology while adding brand new content. <br><br>The new "Special Weapons And Tactics" (SWAT) themed modification will continue the goal of utmost realism set by Uncrossable Parallel. Ingame environments will be entirely based in USA, and will be accurate representations of the locations response teams experience in their real life duties. <br><br>Uncrossable Parallel will now change it's name to fit alongside UP:CQC as "Uncrossable Parallel: Special Forces" and will continue it's theme of Green Beret military warfare. Uncrossable Parallel: Special Forces is now at 80% development status and is set for an early 2002 release. <br><br>Finally, a brand new website is now online for Uncrossable Parallel: Close Quarters Combat at:<br><A HREF="http://www.planethalflife.com/uncrossable/cqc" target=_new>http://www.planethalflife.com/uncrossable/cqc</A><br><br>The Uncrossable Parallel: Special Forces website is now at:<br><A HREF="http://www.planethalflife.com/uncrossable/sf" target=_new>http://www.planethalflife.com/uncrossable/sf</A>"</span></td></tr></table>
</td>
