<table><tr><td valign=top><img src='images/icon_hl.gif' alt='Halflife' border=0></td><td width="100%" valign=top><IMG SRC="http://www.planethalflife.com/uncrossable/newmedia/pipe03s.jpg" align=left width=175> <IMG SRC="http://www.planethalflife.com/uncrossable/newmedia/pipe04s.jpg" align=right width=175> The <A HREF="http://www.planethalflife.com/uncrossable/index.html" target=_new>Uncrossable Parallel</A> website has been updated with some pics of UP_Pipeline, seen on the right and left here, 3 more can be viewed on their <A HREF="http://www.planethalflife.com/uncrossable/index.html" target=_new>news page</A> and more game shots can be viewed in their <A HREF="http://www.planethalflife.com/uncrossable/media.html" target=_new>media section</A>.<br><br>Reading the <A HREF="http://www.planethalflife.com/uncrossable/info.html" target=_new>information</A> section it says:<br><span class=quote>Uncrossable Parallel will feature a diverse range of features that will distance it from other "realism" mods. We have a talented team, dedicated to creating the best game possible. </span><br><br>The game is still in it's Alpha stages, and no news is given to it's aimed released date yet.</td></tr></table>
