<tr>
<td bgcolor="#CECECE" class="btext" width="100%"><b>Voice Technology</b> - <span class=bsmall>posted by  <a class='nNewsMailLink' href='mailto:StealthBuda@barrysworld.com'>StealthBuda</a> on Wed 10 October 2001 06:58:41 | <a href="comments.php?section=4&index=387" class=blink>Comments (0)</a></span></td>
<td bgcolor="#CECECE" width=17><img src="images/item_icon.gif" width="17" height="17" alt="" border="0"></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td bgcolor="#EEEEEE" colspan=2 class=news>
<table><tr><td valign=top><img src='images/icon_hl.gif' alt='Halflife' border=0></td><td width="100%" valign=top>Over at <A HREF="http://www.3dactionplanet.com/" class=colourise target=_new>3D Action Planet</A> they've put up a discussion between Catachan & NeonRonin about the inbuilt half-life voice technology.  Read it <A HREF="http://www.3dactionplanet.com/features/editorials/pcpvoice/" class=colourise target=_new>here</A>.<br><br>Here's a snippet:<br><span class=quote>Catachan: The problem with 3rd party software is that if something goes wrong on the server end of it, everything goes down in flames. A Half-Life voice server, on the other hand, will keep on going until the entire thing goes, meaning you will be using voice chat right up until you leave the game.<br><br>NeonRonin: So instead of making the game engine as lean and fast as possible, you think burdening it down with features that result in obnoxious behavior, slowing the game down bandwidth wise and CPU wise, is a good thing?<br></span></td></tr></table>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
